The paper involves the use of generative models for data augmentation and improving the quality of predictive models in fMRI data analysis. This falls under the domain of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL) as fMRI data analysis involves processing and analyzing language-related brain activity.
